getDimensions

public com.badlogic.gdx.math.Vector2 getDimensions()
Description copied from interface: PhysicsBody
Returns the dimensions of the the box surrounding the body. For example: If the body is in the shape of a circle with the radius 2 this method returns the box around the circle. This box will have a width and a height of 4. (The diameter in each direction).

Specified by:
getDimensions in interface PhysicsBody
Returns:
dimension of body

calculateDimensions

public void calculateDimensions()
This method calculates only the dimensions of the body, so if the body consist of two Fixture, each having a Shape that do not intercept each with other, this method will calculate the box surrounding them both. Used to force a calculation of the body's dimensions. This should only be called if the body's fixtures has been altered.

Specified by:
calculateDimensions in interface PhysicsBody
